{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8fd70e4f-abc5-4d87-b81f-969105ae0536","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package with the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (includes framework, adapter, and test SDK)\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this -->\n<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n\n<!-- Replace Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk with -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n```\n\n**Your test code (`OrderServiceTests.cs`) needs no changes** — the `using Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace and attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout(5000)]`, `Assert.*`) are all the same in MSTest v3.\n\nWant me to apply these changes and verify the project builds?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f6e92fef-8268-4d28-ab63-37e903f79b99","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has an old-style MSTest project that uses:\n1. Assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` (MSTest v1 style)\n2. `net462` target framework\n3. Old `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` version\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3, they need to:\n\n1. Replace the assembly reference with MSTest NuGet packages (MSTestV2 packages: `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`), or better yet, use the MSTest meta-package for v3.\n\n\n2. Update the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a newer version, though their current `net462` target framework is already compatible with MSTest v3 since it supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above.\n3. The cleanest approach is to use the `MSTest` meta-package version 3.x, which bundles both the framework and adapter together.\n\nThe migration steps are straightforward: remove the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`, add a package reference to `MSTest` v3.8.3 o